WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, and happy Easter. It's Sunday, April fifth, twenty

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
twenty-six. I'm your daily briefing, and we've got a big

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
one. Let's start with the headline: the missing pilot is

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
home. After two days behind enemy lines in the mountains

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
of Iran, with Tehran offering a sixty-thousand dollar bounty and

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
two rescue helicopters taking fire, the U-S military pulled off

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
the extraction. He's alive and receiving medical treatment. That's the

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
best news out of this war in weeks. But the

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
clock is already ticking on something else. President Trump issued

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
a forty-eight hour ultimatum yesterday demanding Iran reopen the Strait

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
of Hormuz or face, quote, all hell. That deadline expires

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
tomorrow, Monday, April sixth. Iran's response? They called it helpless

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
and unbalanced. This is now the fourth time Trump has

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
set a Hormuz deadline and moved it. The pattern: dramatic

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
threat, quiet diplomatic extension. But each iteration raises the stakes.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Indirect negotiations are happening via Pakistan, with Vice President Vance

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
and Iran's parliament speaker talking through intermediaries. The question isn't

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
whether he'll follow through tomorrow. It's whether the repeated escalation

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
makes it harder to back down. Meanwhile, the D-H-S shutdown

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
hit day fifty. The Senate passed a funding bill, but

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
the House is on Easter recess until April fourteenth. Thirty-five

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
thousand workers missed paychecks. Five hundred and ten have quit

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
permanently. No resolution before mid-April. Now for the really exciting

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
stuff. Artemis Two is on flight day four, deep in

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
space, preparing for tomorrow's lunar flyby. The window runs from

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
two forty-five to nine forty P-M Eastern. The crew will

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
surpass the Apollo thirteen distance record by over four thousand

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
miles, reaching two hundred fifty-two thousand seven hundred fifty-seven miles

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
from Earth. There's a planned communications blackout around five forty-seven

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
P-M when Orion passes behind the Moon. Four humans, farther

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
from home than anyone has ever been. On the A-I

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
front, Anthropic introduced a multi-agent harness on Friday for autonomous

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
application development. This is the bridge between Claude as a

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
chatbot and Claude as a system that builds things. They

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
also started billing third-party tools like Open-Claw separately as of

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
April fourth, and raised the max tokens cap to three

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
hundred thousand for batch processing. The private market is hot:

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
Anthropic is the most sought-after trade in secondary markets, though

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
the SpaceX I-P-O might drain capital from everything else. Speaking

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
of which, SpaceX filed confidentially to go public, targeting a

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
one-point-seven-five trillion dollar valuation. Thirty percent allocated to retail investors.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
If completed, it would be the largest I-P-O ever, dwarfing

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
Saudi Aramco's twenty-nine billion debut. Axios A-M ran a deep

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
piece on what they're calling Trump's war wager: the one-point-five

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
trillion dollar defense budget as the transformation of his presidency

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
from populist to wartime interventionist. Defense up forty-two percent. E-P-A

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
cut fifty-two percent. National Science Foundation cut fifty-five percent. The

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
coalition that delivered Trump his second term relies on the

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
programs being gutted to fund the military. Congressional Republicans face

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
what Axios calls a brutal choice. Locally, the U-S fifty

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
bridge demolition started last night. Ramps are closed through April

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
twelfth. Proposition A, the capital improvement sales tax renewal for

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
Cole County, is Tuesday. Two days out. The weather is

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
beautiful. Sixty degrees and sunny in Jefferson City, clear tonight

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
with a low of thirty-eight. Tacoma gets sixty-five and partly

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
sunny. Both cities having a nice Easter. No calendar events

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
today. Easter Sunday. Lunch with Mom and Dad needs a

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
time confirmation. Tomorrow is packed: the Artemis flyby and the

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
Iran ultimatum deadline on the same day. A few things

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
worth noting: you paid your bills yesterday. Ameren, one hundred

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
fifty dollars and eighty cents. J-C Utilities, twenty dollars and

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
fifty cents. American Water, confirmed. Roborock floor accessory ordered and

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
shipped. The adulting energy is strong. And on the creative

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
side, five chapters of The Keeping House in five days.

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
That streak was extraordinary. Saturday was a rest day. Let

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
the well refill. That's your Easter Sunday briefing. The pilot

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
is home, the ultimatum is ticking, and four humans are

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
about to fly behind the moon. Go have lunch with

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:34.000
your parents. Your briefing, delivered.
